cs.LG, cs.SC, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the intersection of machine learning and scientific computing, and proposes a new Differentiable Programming system called Zygote. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SC (Scientific Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses advanced techniques such as mixed-mode, complex and checkpointed differentiation, which are commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper presents a new programming model that enables the incorporation of a large ecosystem of libraries, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
